# Raw Data & Retrieval Scope (AGENTS.md §4)

Raw path layout — three scope levels `product` / `project` / `build` (ADR 0011):

```
global/{type}/<file>                        → product=global, project=global, build=global
{product}/common/{type}/<file>              → product common (project=common, build=common)
{product}/{project}/common/{type}/<file>    → project common (build=common)
{product}/{project}/{build}/{type}/<file>   → build truth
```

| Segment | Meaning | Purpose |
|---------|---------|---------|
| `global` | Enterprise shared (`product`=`project`=`build`=`global`) | All products: generic tools, industry practices, common datasheets |
| `{product}/common` | Shared across all projects in a product | Platform architecture, naming, cross-project SOPs |
| `{product}/{project}/common` | Shared across all builds in a project | Project-wide knowledge, not board-specific wiring |
| `{build}` | Specific hardware build | Build truth: schematics and docs for that revision |

`global` and `common` are reserved — never ordinary product/project/build slugs.

Folders `note`, `sch`, `sop`, `datasheet`, `fa` → `document_type` via `config/default.yaml` → `data_layout.document_type_folders`.

V2 ingest metadata: schematic `pages` sidecar (per-page components/nets); datasheet `supply_voltage`/`pin_count`/`package`; FA keywords on `failure_analysis`; `components.json` built at index time.

## Ingestion

- Derive `product`, `project`, `build`, `document_type` from path — never hardcode names in `src/`.
- Write to `data/processed/` mirroring `data/raw/` (`.md` + optional `.meta.json`).
- Use metadata field `build`, never `board`.

## Retrieval

- Honor `retrieval.scope_inheritance` (default `true`).
- Filter `product=P, project=X, build=Y` → expand upward: build → project `common` → product `common` → `global`.
- Rank: build-specific > project `common` > product `common` > `global`.

## Answers

- LLM context headers include `scope`, `project`, `build` (`generation/context.py`).
- Answers must label conclusions by scope; build-specific evidence overrides common/global when they conflict.
- Shared prompt rules: `prompts/_shared/scope_rules.md`.

## V1 formats

PDF, Markdown, TXT, Excel, Word. Skip `.key` / `.numbers` with a clear log until parsers exist.

